KEY POINTS 
Annotations: Use @WebServlet for simpler configuration.
Servlet Mapping: Use web.xml for explicit configurations or older Java versions.
Asynchronous Communication: Combine with AJAX or Fetch API for real-time chat.
Project Overview
The ChatMate Application is a simple web-based chat application that demonstrates the use of Java Servlets to handle HTTP requests and responses. Users can send messages through a web form, and the application responds with dynamically generated responses.

Features
Handle HTTP GET and POST requests using Servlets.
Dynamically generate chat responses.
Simple HTML form integration for user input.
URL mapping and configuration using annotations or web.xml.
Prerequisites
Java Development Kit (JDK): Version 8 or later.
Apache Tomcat: Servlet container for deployment.
Integrated Development Environment (IDE): Eclipse, IntelliJ IDEA, or any Java-supporting IDE.
Maven (optional): For dependency management.
